Between the weekends of August 30 and December 20, 2019, Jehovah’s Witnesses, will present one of the largest global conventions, which will span across six continents and over 200 countries. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The convention will be presented in over 400 languages, in Lagos and surrounding cities, will also host a global series of three-day conventions featuring the theme “Love Never Fails.” It is expected to have in attendance about 45,000 at 39 conventions to be held at Lekki, Badagry and Daluwon Assembly Halls. According to Mr. Jama Onwubuariri, a local representative for Jehovah’s Witnesses, the convention program will examine how Bible principles help people in practical ways. Onwubuariri said the Friday programme will address how love can help people surmount obstacles such as a troubled upbringing, chronic illness, or poverty.